Property indicating the component has finished its initialization squence, for instance setting default values than can be read from other component
This property is set as reflected attribute to be able to trigger a mutation for consumer components

members.name: useBetaEndpoint
members.description: Flag indicating if the beta endpoint for Microsoft Graph API should be used

members.name: entityTypes
members.description: The Microsoft Search entity types to query

members.name: defaultQueryText
members.description:
The default query text to apply.
Query string parameter and search box have priority over this value during first load

members.description: The search query template to use. Support tokens https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/search-concept-query-template

members.name: selectedFields
members.description:
Search managed properties to retrieve for results and usable in the results template. 
Comma separated. Refer to the [Microsoft Search API documentation](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/search-api-overview?view=graph-rest-1.0&preserve-view=true#scope-search-based-on-entity-types) to know what properties can be used according to entity types.

members.description: The number of results to show per results page

members.description: The number of pages to display in the pagination control

members.name: enableResultTypes
members.description: Flag indicating if Micrsoft Search result types should be applied in results

members.name: connectionIds
members.description: If "entityTypes" contains "externalItem", specify the connection id of the external source

members.name: enableModification
members.description: Indicates whether spelling modifications are enabled. If enabled, the user will get the search results for the corrected query in case of no results for the original query with typos.

members.name: enableSuggestion
members.description: Indicates whether spelling suggestions are enabled. If enabled, the user will get the search results for the original search query and suggestions for spelling correction
